name: Arise_Carnival DS - Sales Inquiries - Booking created ~ BEG

audioContentItems.fileTranscript: Carnival Fun Ships, this is [Agent Name]. May I have your name, please?
My name is Alice Test.
Hi, Alice. Are you currently booked on one of our Fun Ships or working with a Travel Advisor?
No, I’m calling in to see if you can help me plan my cruise.
I’ll be happy to get your cruise booked today.
May I have your phone number?
Thank you!
Florida.
Thank you.
Alice, may I have your email address?
Sure! It's alice test@email.com.
Thank you! May I have your address?
Sure! It's 1 2 3 Maple Street, Miami, Florida, 3 3 1 0 1.
Thank you.
Have you cruised with Carnival before?
No, this is my first cruise.
Welcome to Carnival. I’m so glad you chose to sail with us. Are you celebrating anything special?
I’m just wanting to plan a fun getaway vacation for just myself and my husband.
Fantastic! So, it sounds like you are looking for one cabin for two guests, right?
Yes.
Would anyone traveling have the need for special accommodations or is pregnant?
No.
And to make sure I don’t miss any promotions for you, is anyone traveling an employee of an interline company such as a passenger airline, Amtrak, or UPS or FedEx?
No.
Anyone serve in the U.S. Armed Forces, Canadian National Defense or over the age of 55?
No, not yet.
Has your husband sailed with Carnival before?
No.
And you mentioned earlier, you live in Florida, correct?
Yes
What ship and sail date have you picked out?
I’m interested in sailing on the Carnival Breeze sailing April 1, 2027.
I’m glad you are calling in to book today, that’s a popular time to travel over spring break. Bear with me a moment as I pull that up.

Your cruise will be on the Breeze sailing April 1, 2027, out of the port of Galveston on a 4-day Western Caribbean itinerary. Your boarding time is from 12:30 p.m. to 2:00 p.m. and you will be visiting Cozumel, Mexico with 2 fun days at sea.
Yes, that's the one we want.
Awesome!

Your ship, the Breeze, has 14 passenger decks. It has an adult serenity retreat that is only for guests 21 and older where you can sit back, relax, and smell the sea breeze. It also has a seaside theater where you can watch movies under the stars. There are some great additional food options too, like Guy’s Burger Joint, which has the best burgers.
My husband loves burgers. Sounds good!
Great!

Things included in your cruise are breakfast, lunch, dinner, snacks, ice cream, pizza, comedy shows, and our amazing stage shows. Not included are our spa treatments, alcoholic beverages, carbonated beverages, gratuities, and if you want to try your luck in our casino at sea.
This sounds perfect for us.
Great! Now, let’s find you the best deal for your cruise.
We have a lot of great promotions. I’m seeing the best promotion for you today is our Early Saver Promotion.

The Early Saver promotion guarantees you the lowest rate from the day that you book all the way until two business days prior to your sailing. If at any time the rate drops below what you booked at, you can fill out a price protection form online and have the balance adjusted before final payment or get the difference as an onboard credit after final. Keep in mind this promotion does not allow name changes and if you cancel or move your sailing prior to final payment date it’s only $50 per person fee and the rest of the money gets put towards a future cruise credit which you have 12 months to use.
Okay.

What kind of cabin would you prefer? They're all very spacious. We have an interior cabin with no windows, an Ocean View with a big picture window, a Balcony cabin that gives you both a window and your own private balcony, and our largest option - a Suite, which has even more space and a balcony.
We would like to have a Balcony cabin.
Great choice! That’s my favorite, too.
I’m looking forward to finding you a great balcony.

I found a great cabin for you. It’s on our Lido Deck, Deck 10. There are only 4 cabins left that accommodate 2 guests on this deck so I’m glad you called in today. This will put you in the middle of the ship. Let’s look at the details about your cabin.

Your cabin has 220 square feet, two twin size beds that will convert to a king for you, and your own private balcony. One of the best things about a balcony is how you can enjoy your morning coffee or a glass of wine at night while you enjoy the sounds, smell, and view of the ocean from your own private balcony.
Sounds perfect for us.
Awesome, let me get the pricing for your cabin.
Your cabin is only an average rate of $829 per person including taxes and fees based upon 2 guests in the cabin. Carnival Vacation Protection is $190 for the cabin, giving you a total of $1848.00.

All we need to get started today is a small deposit of $340, which includes activation of your Carnival Vacation Protection. The remaining balance won't be due until your final payment date of 1/16/2027. Would you like to book this with early, late or your-time dining?
Let’s book for a late dining.
Wonderful!
I have the perfect cabin for you, cabin number 10277.
After this call, you will receive an email confirmation. Please read the terms and conditions of your email cruise ticket contract, as you are legally bound by the terms.
Okay.
May I have each name as it appears on their travel documents?
Alice Test 05/14/1985 and James Test 9/24/1984.
Thank you! Just to confirm, that was Alice Test with date of birth 05/14/1985 and you said it was your husband traveling with you, James Test, with his date of birth 9/24/1984?
That is correct.
Is everyone traveling a U.S. Citizen and U.S. Resident?
Yes, we are.
And you mentioned earlier you both live in Florida, correct?
Correct.
Would you like to go ahead and include your prepaid gratuities, or will you be taking care of that onboard?
I think I’ll handle that onboard.
Okay, thanks!
I selected your dinner time as Late Dining as you requested earlier.
Great!
Please choose a 4-digit pin number that is easy for you to remember for security purposes.
How about 2 4 8 7.
2487, got it!
And to confirm does anyone traveling have a special need or pregnant?
No
And you mentioned earlier you were sailing for a fun get away. No special occasions, right?
Correct, not this time. This time it is just for fun.
Thank you!
May I have an alternate contact telephone number?
Sure, my cell phone is 305-222-3333.
Thank you! Would you like a text to be sent to your mobile number for all sailing changes and payment reminders?
Yes, please.
Bear with me a moment as I finish creating your booking.
Okay.
I’m almost done. I’m just putting some additional notes on your booking.

Your booking number is X9SN55. You are sailing on the Breeze doing a 4-day Western Caribbean itinerary. We have you in that amazing balcony cabin, 10277. The total cost of your cruise is $1848 with only your deposit of $340 due today.

Are you taking care of this payment now or would you like to hear more about our partner, Flex Pay, where you could book this for as little as $0 down and pay for up to 24 months with affordable rates?
I’m going to use my Visa Card.
Okay, great!
May I have the name of the card holder?
It is April 2028, and my zip code is 3 3 1 3 3.
Thank you, I have April 2028 and zip code of 33133, correct?
Yes.
Would you like to pay just the deposit of $340 today?
Yes, the deposit only.

As a courtesy for you, we can go ahead and set up Auto Pay for you interest free and split your final payment amount into equal amounts of $71.81 starting on May 1, 2025. Would you like to go ahead and take advantage of this?
Yes, let’s go ahead and set that up.
Okay, perfect.
I see your payment of $340.00 has processed.
I am going to send your cabin confirmation now.

You are all set. Keep in mind that adding or removing a guest will change the average rate per person. Please refer to your confirmation that I am emailing you now or you can go on the website to carnival.com/bookedguest for your electronic documents, boarding pass, travel docs, and penalty information.
Okay.
What state do you live in?
One moment while I grab your cabin.
Thank you!
May I have your email address so we can contact you in case of itinerary changes or voyage delays?​
Let’s use my same email earlier for me at alice test @ email.com and james test @ email.com for my husband.​
Thank you!
May I have the expiration date and billing zip code?
You are now in Secure Mode. Please enter your credit card information.
Yes.
Now that I’ve verified the name of the cardholder, expiration date, zip code, and payment amount, I will be placing you into Secure Mode where I will prompt you to enter your credit card number. ​ ​

During this time, you will be able to hear me, however, I will not be able to hear you. It is important that when entering your credit card number, you are not using speakerphone or a Bluetooth device. ​
After you input your credit card number, Secure Mode will drop, and our call will reconnect, allowing me to hear you again. Then, I can verify payment. Do you have your credit card ready?
Yes.
Do you have any questions before I place you into Secure Mode?​
No.
Thank you for your payment of $340.00. Before I submit, are the last few digits 4444?
Proper travel documentation is due upon embarkation and Carnival highly recommends a passport.
Is there anything else I can help you with today?
That’s all.
Super! As a reminder, you will be receiving an email survey about my service today. I appreciate your feedback.
Sure, you really made this whole process very easy.
Thank you for choosing Carnival and you have a Funtastic day!
It’s my name on the card.​ Alice Test.

settings.text: This simulation will give you practice in handling a beginner call type. You can go through this as many times as desired until you feel confident in the navigation and call flow.
Have your audio and microphone ready. You must complete the test version to receive credit for completion of this simulation. Let's get started.
Call will beep in your ear.​
Make sure you have your Navigator open.​
Click on the 'Carnival Funnel' in the upper left corner in Navigator.​  ​
Click on 'New Booking.'
If the Guest’s phone number does not auto populate, enter the Guest’s phone number in Navigator.​
Type: '305-222-3333' in the Phone number field. Then press 'Enter.'
Click on 'Select' button.
Click on the 'State' field dropdown.
Select 'Florida' from the options.
Capture the lead by asking or verifying phone number, First and Last Name, State, and if the guest doesn’t live in the country of Canada ask or verify the guest’s email address.​
Check 'First Time Cruiser' from the Guest Details.
Check 'Fun (Standard Vacation)' from the 'Reason For Cruising.'
Select '1' In Number of Rooms.
Click on the 'Downward Arrow' next to Prospective Guest checklist.
Click on 'Residency State' dropdown.
Select 'Florida' from the options.
There are two ways we can search for a ship and sailing: 'Quick Search' and 'Find A Cruise.'
If the guest knows which ship and sailing, we click on Quick Search. If the guest does not know, then we click on Find a Cruise. For this call example, we will be using Quick Search.​
After clicking on 'Quick Search', click the dropdown to select the ship first. Then click on the 'Departure Date' to select the date of departure.
Select 'BR -  BREEZE' from the dropdown option.
Now, click on the 'Departure Date' dropdown to select the date of departure.
Scroll down to the preferred date.
Select '04/01/2027 [4] [GLB] [Open]' from the available dates.​
Click on 'Go' button.
You are now on the next page in Navigator with the Sailing information.​
Click on the Itinerary link to open the Pop-Up window.​  ​
Read off the itinerary details on the page, then click Close or the red X on the itinerary Pop-Up to close it.
Using our Service Aid Resources, the Agent gives a short 30 second ship presentation tailored to the guest to spark interest and add value.
Click on "What's Included.'
Using our Service Aid Resources, give a What’s Included presentation to this guest who is a First-time cruiser by reading one of the 4 options listed here.​
Review the promotions on the sailing.  ​
Using our Script Service Aid Resource, tell the guest the promotion and any advisories.​  ​
When we click the Cabin Category, it will highlight in yellow and then show the corresponding information about that Cabin Category on the right. ​
Click on the 'Deck Plan.'
Look for a cabin in green which means that cabin is available for the number of guests we entered in Navigator.​  ​
Then advise the deck and if the cabin is in the forward (front), middle, or aft (back) of the ship.​  ​
After advising location, click on the green cabin.
Advise the cabin details.
Click on 'Pre-Pricing.'
Give pricing based upon the details of what was selected.
Advise the deposit amount and final payment on the screen. Then ask for the sale using an assumptive statement.​  ​
Click on 'Deck Plan.'
Click on the 'Book Button' to start the booking process.  ​  ​
Using our Script Service Aid Resource, advise the Cruise Ticket Contract advisory.​
Type: 'Alice' in the first Name field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Click on 'Title' dropdown and select 'MRS' from the option.
Type:  '05/14/1985' in the Date of Birth Field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Type: 'Test' in the Last name field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Type: 'James' in the 'First Name' field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Click on 'Title' dropdown and Select 'MR' from the option.
Type: '04/24/1984' in the James 'Date of Birth.' and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
We select the country of citizenship under PN (Person’s Nationality), enter country of residency under Residency, and resident state under ReState.​
Click on the 'PN' dropdown and select 'US' from the available option.
Again click on the 'PN' dropdown and select 'US' from the option.
Click on the Residency dropdown.
Select 'US' from the option.
Click on the Residency dropdown.
Select 'US' from the option.
Now click on the 'Re-state' option for James Field.
Select 'Florida' from the option.
Ask and enter dining and pin number that the Guest chooses.
Type: '2 4 8 7' in the 'Pin Field' and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Click on 'Guest Info' at the top to continue entering in booking information.​
Ask the questions about special needs, pregnancy, and special occasions. If there are any, select the blank box to the right of the Guest under Pax Code to enter it in.​ ​ ​
Type: 'alicetest@email.com' in the Alice's email field. And click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Type: 'jamestest@email.com' in the James's email field. and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Ask about alternative phone numbers. If the Guest has a mobile or home phone number they want to provide we enter it in.

If the guest gives their mobile number and it is their primary number, select the box “Is Mobile Primary.” With a mobile number we ask and enter if the Guest would like to receive text alerts by selecting Y (yes) or N (No). Then, select if the Guest would like to receive all text alerts, sailing text alerts only, or payment text alerts only from the dropdown box.
Type  '305-222-3333' in the Mobile Phone field.
Click on the checkbox of 'Is Mobile Primary?'
Next click on the 'Text Preferred I N D' dropdown.
Select 'Y' from the option.
Click on the 'Text Alert Type' dropdown.
Select  'ALL' from the option.
Click on  'Create Booking.'
Click on 'Main Tab.'
Click on 'History.'
Click on the 'Add Comments.'
Type: 'ADVISED GUEST CRUISE TICKET CONTRACT AND EARLY SAVER RULES,' Then hit the 'Enter' button.

settings.expectedValue: ADVISED GUEST CRUISE TICKET CONTRACT AND EARLY SAVER RULES.

settings.text: Click on the 'Save' button.
Click on 'Manage Funds' and select 'Credit/Gift Card Payment.'​  ​
Click on the Checkbox, next to Alice.
Click on the 'Select Cardholder' Dropdown.
Select 'Test Alice – Seq 1,' from the option.
Type: '0428' in the Expiry field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Type: '33133' in the Zip Code field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Type: '340' in the Amount field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
If it is available on the sailing, then advise Auto Pay or Schedule final payment options. If the guest wants to set it up, select the option from the dropdown under Sch Pmt.​
Select '21 months Payment Plan' from the option.
Click on the 'Secure Mode' Icon.
After confirming payment, click on Submit.​
Check to confirm payment has processed. This can be seen under Payments and also in the Booking History.​
Click on 'Cabin Report' by selecting the icon at the top of the Navigator or from the booking panel on the right.
Select the box next to each email.  Then, click Send. ​
Type: 'alicetest@email.com.' In the 'Survey Email' Field and click 'enter' on your keyboard.
Now that the booking is completed and the call is done, click the X on the tab in Navigator to close the tab.
Congratulations! You have completed this simulation.
